Men carry a tower of strength so well that we often neglect our emotional and mental needs. 
But how can we love if we are broken?
A man can not give what he lacks. To love another, we must first look within to fix what’s broken and heal past traumas. 
Even the most robust towers can crumble if great care is not taken. 
To reciprocate love, we must first master self love.
